---
title: One-Pot Italian Vegetable & Shrimp Soup with Kale, Israeli Couscous & Garlic Bread
description: No matter the weather, it’s tough not to crave a big bowl of soup (i.e. the culinary equivalent of a bear hug). Enter this hearty, soul-warming veggie rendition. It’s chock-full of goodness—that’s to say carrots, onion, crushed tomatoes, a bevy of Italian herbs and spices, chewy couscous, and tender kale. And because no good brothy bowl is complete without something delicious for dunking, we’re also throwing in a side of toasty, buttery garlic bread. Soup’s on!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6447d3165b773e366f0f87c3-a3fa52d9.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/65ba9d75f6debb5c45b6ba3a.pdf
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
time required: 35m
nutrition:
  calories: 800 kcal
  fat: 27 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 86 g
  sugar: 24 g
  protein: 35 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 1830 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pot-italian-vegetable-and-shrimp-soup-65ba9d75f6debb5c45b6ba3a
course: main course
---

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice @onion{1}. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{6%ounces} into ¼-inch-thick rounds. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounces}.

Rinse @shrimp{10%ounces} under cold water. Pat shrimp dry with #paper towels{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pot{} over medium-high heat. Add shrimp; cook, stirring occasionally, until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoons} in a large pot over medium-high heat. Add onion and carrots; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are lightly browned and slightly softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir @Italian Seasoning{1%tablespoon} and garlic into pot with veggies. Cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @crushed tomatoes{13.76%ounces}, @veggie stock concentrate{3}, @water{3%cups}, and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer. Cook until carrots are just softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Once carrots are just softened, stir in @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounces} and kale. Cook until couscous is tender and kale is wilted, ~{8-10%minutes}. Taste and season generously with salt and pepper.

Once kale is wilted, stir in shrimp.

While soup cooks, halve @demi-baguette{1} lengthwise.

Place @butter{2%tablespoons} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until just softened, ~{10-15%seconds}. Stir in @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} and season with salt and pepper.

Toast baguette halves, then spread cut sides with garlic butter. Halve each piece on a diagonal.

Divide soup between bowls. Sprinkle with @parmesan cheese{3%tablespoons} and a pinch of @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} to taste. Serve with garlic bread on the side.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.